  "text": "## Formula Evaluation Chain in LibreOffice Calc\n\n### Overview\nThe formula evaluation chain in LibreOffice Calc consists of four main phases: parsing/compilation, cell storage, recalculation scheduling, and interpretation/evaluation.\n\n### 1. Parsing & Compilation Phase\n**Key File**: `sc/source/core/tool/compiler.cxx` and `sc/inc/compiler.hxx`\n**Key Class**: `ScCompiler` (extends `formula::FormulaCompiler`)\n\nThe compiler takes a formula string like `=SUM(A1:A10)` and tokenizes it into a bytecode representation (token array). The `ScCompiler` class:\n- Parses the formula using formula::FormulaCompiler's tokenization engine\n- Handles various address conventions (A1, R1C1, etc.)\n- Resolves named ranges and external references\n- Produces a `ScTokenArray` (bytecode) that the interpreter can execute\n\n### 2. Formula Cell Storage Phase\n**Key File**: `sc/inc/formulacell.hxx` and `sc/source/core/data/formulacell.cxx`\n**Key Class**: `ScFormulaCell`\n\nThe `ScFormulaCell` class represents a single cell containing a formula. It:\n- Stores the token array (formula bytecode) in member variable `pCode`\n- Maintains dirty/recalc state via flags like `bDirty`, `bCompile`, `bTableOpDirty`\n- Caches the last computed result in `ScFormulaResult aResult`\n- Tracks formula dependencies for listening/broadcasting\n- Supports formula groups for vectorized calculation of multiple cells with the same formula\n- Implements the `Interpret()` method that triggers evaluation\n\n### 3. Recalculation Scheduling Phase\n**Key Files**: `sc/inc/document.hxx`, `sc/source/core/data/documen7.cxx`\n**Key Class**: `ScDocument` (which manages recalculation state and scheduling)\n**Key Enum**: `ScRecalcMode` (defined in `include/formula/tokenarray.hxx`)\n\nThe recalculation system:\n- Uses `ScRecalcMode` flags to determine when cells need recalculation:\n  - `ALWAYS`: Always recalculate\n  - `WHEN_STORED`: Recalculate when stored (default)\n  - `MUST_AFTER_IMPORT`: Must recalculate after import\n  - Others: Control volatile functions, conditional recalc\n- Maintains a formula tree (doubly-linked list) of all formula cells via `pFormulaTree` and `pEOFormulaTree` pointers in `ScDocument`\n- `ScDocument::PutInFormulaTree()` adds cells to the recalc queue\n- `ScDocument::CalcFormulaTree()` iterates through the formula tree and recalculates dirty cells\n- Tracks dependencies through listeners/broadcasters for automatic recalculation\n\n### 4. Interpretation/Evaluation Phase\n**Key File**: `sc/source/core/inc/interpre.hxx` and `sc/source/core/tool/interpr*.cxx` (8 files)\n**Key Class**: `ScInterpreter`\n\nThe interpreter evaluates the compiled token array:\n- Spans 8 implementation files (interpr1.cxx through interpr8.cxx) due to size\n- `ScInterpreter::Interpret()` is the main entry point that walks the token array\n- Implements all built-in functions (SUM, AVERAGE, IF, etc.) as individual methods\n- Maintains an operand stack for intermediate values during evaluation\n- Handles type conversions between numeric, string, and array values\n- Returns results that are cached in the `ScFormulaCell`\n\n### Execution Flow Example: `=SUM(A1:A10)`\n\n1. **Compilation** (compiler.cxx):\n   - Formula string `\"=SUM(A1:A10)\"` is parsed\n   - Tokenized as: [OP_SUM] [OP_RANGE A1:A10]\n   - Stored as token array in ScTokenArray\n\n2. **Storage** (formulacell.cxx):\n   - ScFormulaCell created with the token array\n   - Cell marked as `bDirty = true`\n   - References to A1:A10 registered as listeners\n\n3. **Scheduling** (documen7.cxx):\n   - Cell added to formula tree via `PutInFormulaTree()`\n   - When A1 or any cell in A1:A10 changes:\n     - Dependent cell is marked dirty\n     - Added to formula tree for recalculation\n   - `CalcFormulaTree()` is called to recalculate all dirty cells\n\n4. **Evaluation** (interpr1-8.cxx):\n   - `ScInterpreter::Interpret()` executes token array\n   - SUM function handler collects values from A1:A10\n   - Computes sum and returns numeric result\n   - Result cached in `ScFormulaCell::aResult`\n   - Cell marked as clean (`bDirty = false`)\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n- **Lazy Evaluation**: Formulas are only recalculated when marked dirty\n- **Dependency Tracking**: Formula cells listen to their referenced cells\n- **Token Array Caching**: Compilation is cached in ScFormulaCell to avoid recompilation\n- **Formula Grouping**: Multiple cells with the same formula can share the token array\n- **Incremental Recalc**: Only dirty cells are recalculated via the formula tree"
}

